{
  "texts": [
    "The COIG dataset consists of 191K Chinese instructions categorized into five types.",
    "Translated instructions are derived from open-source datasets, and the translation process involves three stages: automatic translation, manual verification, and manual correction.",
    "Exam instructions are primarily sourced from Chinese college entrance exams, high school entrance exams, and civil service exams.",
    "Human value alignment instructions consist of two series-one focusing on general human value alignment in Chinese regions, and the other on human value alignment specific to certain countries or regional cultures.",
    "Counterfactual correction multi-round chat are built based on the CN-DBpedia knowledge graph dataset (Xu et al, 2017), addressing hallucination issues in LLMs."
  ]
}